text: South Grafton High School (abbreviated as SGHS) is a government-funded co- educational comprehensive secondary day school, located in , in the Mid North Coast region of New South Wales, Australia. In 2018 the school enrolled approximately 520 students from Year 7 to Year 12, of whom 21 percent identified as Indigenous Australians and three percent were from a language background other than English. The school is operated by the NSW Department of Education; the principal is Kristine Pizarro. ==See also== * List of government schools in New South Wales * List of schools in Northern Rivers and Mid North Coast * Education in Australia * Grafton High School ==References== ==External links== * * NSW Schools website Category:Public high schools in New South Wales South High School
